{
  "stem": "10353.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "On May 9th, in the evening, we were doing our usual work cleaning up the kitchen around 9:00, 9:30 in the evening, when my fellow worker, whom I refer to as a German Jew, young, younger man, we were cleaning up the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was looking down from the second floor window.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he saw some people in strange uniforms.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he told me in German, he says, oh, he says, they must be some French prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We didn't pay too much attention, until about 50 minutes later, a Russian tank moved through.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then the Russian army started to move in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we knew already there was a whole, whole upheaval in the camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Everybody's dancing and jumping, you know, the Russians came in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "With us knowing that-- the way typhoid was breaking out-- we were determined the following morning to leave camp and to go towards Prague, which we did.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We walked for about six to eight kilometers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had to turn back, because the Germans were still fighting on and there was still heavy activity going on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So we went back to the-- to the camp-- to the Dresdner Kaserne.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we waited 'til the following morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The following morning around 4:00 o'clock in the morning, we got up and we started to walk towards Prague.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we walked and we walked and we walked all day long, 'til around noontime we caught onto a Russian column, a horse-- a horse-drawn wagon.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we begged them that they should take us on, which they did.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they took us on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we traveled with them, until we came to a village in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We didn't know where we were, but we traveled with them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they-- they drove into a farmhouse.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
